==Japanese==
===Hiragana letter===
'''で''' (de)

For a list of words starting with this hiragana see: [[Wiktionary:Japanese index て|Japanese index て]]
====Alternate forms====
*[[デ]] (de) - katakana


===Etymology===
originally an alteration of [[にて]] (''ni te''), later treated as a conjugation of the copula だ (''da'')

===Particle===
'''で''' (''[[de]]'')

# indicating being at a location.
#* [[ここ]]'''で'''やすみたい。
#*:[[ここ]]'''で'''やすみたい。
#*:''[[koko|Koko]] '''de''' yasumitai.''
#*:I want to rest [[here]] ('''at''' this location).
# indicating instrumental, [[with]], [[by]].
#* [[自転車]]'''で'''行きましょう。
#*:[[じてんしゃ]]'''で'''いきましょう。
#*:''[[jitensha|Jitensha]] '''de''' ikimashō.''
#*:Let's go '''by''' [[bicycle]].

====Synonyms====
# [[にて]] (''ni te'')

===Verb===
'''で''' ([[de]])
# the て-form of [[だ]].


